To "shout out" is to express a greeting or to acknowledge someone of importance.  A "shout out" is typically bestowed in an affectionate manner.  It is also synonymous with "giving props."  

Example:  "I like to give a shout out to my partner in rhyme,  Michael D. Broda. I also like to give a shout out to Margaux,  Natalie,  Liz,  Megan,  Max, Jen, and the Crazy Jim-  stay fresh!"